verbose_text: The global prevalence of hyperuricemia, defined as serum uric acid (SUA) levels of> = 6.8 mg/dl in the extracellular fluid, has increased over the past few decades; it continues to rise in developed countries such as the United States (21.2-21.6%) and in rapidly developing countries such as China (13.3%), where major shifts in lifestyle and diet have occurred over the past two decades [XREF_BIBR - XREF_BIBR].
